# GPSoftware Provenance Record: GPL License Authorization

The following documentation establishes an explicit corporate license grant from
GPSoftware for the Directory Opus 5 Amiga codebase used in this repository.

*Note: This document contains heavily condensed and redacted transcripts of the
original 2023 communications to preserve personal privacy, remove unrelated
technical forum chatter, and focus strictly on the licensing outcome. Full,
unedited message archives are maintained privately by the repository owner for
legal verification.*

---

### Part 1: Developer Clarification & CEO Referral
In January 2023, an inquiry regarding the open-source reuse of the Directory
Opus 5 Amiga source code was made to original developer Jonathan ("Jon") Potter,
who referred the matter directly to the corporate ownership of GPSoftware.

```text
From: Jonathan Potter (Directory Opus Developer)
Date: Mon, Jan 16, 2023
To: Me <address redacted>

"Greg would have even less memory of it than I do... Feel free to email him at
greg@gpsoft.com.au if you like... The original readme.txt (written by me)
referred only to APL..."
```

---

### Part 2: Explicit Email Authorization from CEO Dr. Greg Perry
Direct follow-up with GPSoftware Managing Director, Dr. Greg Perry, to formally
authorize releasing an independent, non-commercial adaptation of the Amiga
codebase on GitHub under the GNU General Public License (GPL).

```text
From: Me <address redacted>
Date: Mon, Jan 16, 2023 at 10:52 AM
To: Dr. Greg Perry <greg@gpsoft.com.au>

Dear Dr. Greg Perry,
[...] My memory is that when the DOpus Amiga source was released in response to
the fundraiser in 2012: You released it as dual-license with a choice of APL
or GPL...

---

From: Dr. Greg Perry <greg@gpsoft.com.au>
Date: Tue, Jan 17, 2023 at 2:28 AM
To: Me <address redacted>

[...] If you want to put it on GitHub, you have our permission to do that. We do
not express any rights of the code providing it is not used to create commercial
products. The Amiga code is in no way related to the windows version of
Directory Opus.

---

From: Me <address redacted>
Date: Tue, Jan 17, 2023 at 11:01 AM
To: Dr. Greg Perry <greg@gpsoft.com.au>

Dear Dr. Greg Perry,

Thank you so much for your answer.

Just to clarify so no-one can come after me later, telling me what I do is
illegal. Are you giving me permission to put my adaption of the code on GitHub
under the GPL license. I'm just learning Amiga programming again, and have no
commercial interests.

---

From: Dr. Greg Perry <greg@gpsoft.com.au>
Date: Tue, Jan 17, 2023 at 11:06 PM
To: Me <address redacted>

Yes. You have permission to do that.
```
